45
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:32,900
Oh yeah, did you hear?

46
00:03:32,983 --> 00:03:34,692
Apparently someone
developed a new plugin

47
00:03:34,775 --> 00:03:37,692
that allows you to actually
talk to the Actors!

48
00:03:37,775 --> 00:03:39,692
Quiet, that stuff is
against the rules!

49
00:03:39,775 --> 00:03:41,192
If the admins see you
with it installed,

50
00:03:41,275 --> 00:03:42,775
they'll delete your account!

51
00:03:42,858 --> 00:03:46,358
Chill out, scaredy cat.
It's not like I'd ever use it.

52
00:03:46,442 --> 00:03:47,567
[VANILLA]
You better not.

53
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:49,358
I'd die if I couldn't
see my boy anymore!

54
00:03:49,442 --> 00:03:50,942
Jeez, there's always
someone trying to make

55
00:03:51,025 --> 00:03:53,233
a quick buck with all
these plugins and hacks.

56
00:03:53,317 --> 00:03:55,983
This game really cracks
down hard on rulebreakers.

57
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,733
[FEMALE PLAYER 9D yelps]

58
00:04:00,358 --> 00:04:01,275
[FEMALE PLAYER 9F]
What happened?

59
00:04:01,358 --> 00:04:02,983
[MALE PLAYER 9B]
Are you all right?

60
00:04:08,483 --> 00:04:11,192
Another Saturday wasted in
supplementary classes.

61
00:04:11,275 --> 00:04:12,525
Hey, guys.

62
00:04:12,608 --> 00:04:15,608
Whoa, is everybody
okay? Who died?

63
00:04:15,692 --> 00:04:17,775
Well, uh.

64
00:04:17,858 --> 00:04:19,067
What did you say?

65
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:21,900
Some asshole is out there
hurting stray cats?

66
00:04:21,983 --> 00:04:24,108
[HINATA] Yeah. We were
out last night, and...

67
00:04:24,192 --> 00:04:25,650
[clattering]

68
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,442
[BOTH gasp]

69
00:04:27,525 --> 00:04:29,150
[HINATA] We heard a racket
and went to check it out.

70
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:32,067
[FEMALE PLAYER 9E growling]

71
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,192
[BOTH gasp]

72
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:37,275
[HINATA]
Hold it!

73
00:04:37,358 --> 00:04:38,525
[gasps]

74
00:04:41,358 --> 00:04:44,483
There. Now, let's get you-- Huh?

75
00:04:44,567 --> 00:04:46,150
Both the guy and
the cat ran off

76
00:04:46,233 --> 00:04:47,608
before we could do
much to help them.

77
00:04:47,692 --> 00:04:49,108
My theory is this:

78
00:04:49,192 --> 00:04:51,567
he was attempting to catch
the cat and it scratched him.

79
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,983
And then he fell down the
stairs in the back alley.

80
00:04:54,067 --> 00:04:55,733
Which is what caused
all of the ruckus.

81
00:04:55,817 --> 00:04:57,983
[RYO gasps]
But was the cat all right?

82
00:04:58,067 --> 00:04:59,817
It did have some
cuts and bruises.

83
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,567
But nothing severe
enough that we'd have to

84
00:05:01,650 --> 00:05:04,233
track it down and bring it
to a vet, I think.

85
00:05:04,317 --> 00:05:05,775
That sick bastard.

86
00:05:05,858 --> 00:05:07,358
What did he look like?

87
00:05:07,442 --> 00:05:09,442
We couldn't get a
good look at his face.

88
00:05:09,525 --> 00:05:12,025
But he was wearing
a gray hoodie.

89
00:05:12,108 --> 00:05:14,150
And he had a medium build.

90
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:16,942
If he ran off immediately
after falling down the stairs,

91
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,192
then he must be someone
quite athletic, as well.

92
00:05:19,275 --> 00:05:21,358
I'm gonna find him and kill him!

93
00:05:21,442 --> 00:05:24,442
Wait, Ryo. People who harm
small animals tend to be

94
00:05:24,525 --> 00:05:27,108
repeat offenders, who will
inevitably strike again.

95
00:05:27,192 --> 00:05:28,692
Instead of aimlessly searching,

96
00:05:28,775 --> 00:05:30,483
we should organize a
neighborhood watch.

97
00:05:30,567 --> 00:05:32,900
[RYO] A kitty
protection patrol? I'm in!

98
00:05:32,983 --> 00:05:36,108
[MITSUKI] Ryo. Don't you have
supplementary classes today?

99
00:05:36,192 --> 00:05:38,442
[RYO]
This is way more important!

100
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:44,775
Hey! Show yourself, you scumbag!

101
00:05:53,192 --> 00:05:55,692
It looks like there
aren't any cats out today.

102
00:05:55,775 --> 00:05:57,442
They're all probably
hiding somewhere

103
00:05:57,525 --> 00:05:59,025
because they're freaked out.

104
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:01,108
[HINATA] Someone's
harming cats in the area.

105
00:06:01,192 --> 00:06:02,817
[MITSUKI]
Thank you for your time.

106
00:06:05,983 --> 00:06:08,275
[SATSUMA] All the
information is on the flyer.

107
00:06:08,358 --> 00:06:10,900
Why's no one
taking them from me?

108
00:06:10,983 --> 00:06:13,108
It's because you come
off so intimidating.

109
00:06:13,192 --> 00:06:15,275
Would it kill you to be
a bit more friendly?

110
00:06:15,358 --> 00:06:22,150
Yeah, yeah. Let's protect the
kitties together, little boy.

111
00:06:22,233 --> 00:06:24,858
[cries]

112
00:06:24,942 --> 00:06:26,775
Well. C plus for effort.

113
00:06:26,858 --> 00:06:28,983
[RYO]
Shut the hell up and help me!

114
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:32,692
[BLACK CAT meows]

115
00:06:32,775 --> 00:06:33,525
[ALL]
Hm?

116
00:06:33,608 --> 00:06:34,817
Hey, it's the Black Kitty!

117
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,358
You staying safe
out there, girl?

118
00:06:36,442 --> 00:06:37,733
[BLACK CAT meows]

119
00:06:37,817 --> 00:06:38,942
Don't worry, we're making sure

120
00:06:39,025 --> 00:06:41,233
not to come out unless
we really have to.

121
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,608
We're being super careful,
just like you said!

122
00:06:43,692 --> 00:06:46,108
Aren't you awfully chatty today.
Want some food, baby?

123
00:06:46,192 --> 00:06:47,525
[BLACK CAT]
No, listen!

124
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:49,025
Someone mentioned they saw
the guy you're looking for

125
00:06:49,108 --> 00:06:51,025
near the school, so I
ran over here to tell you!

126
00:06:51,108 --> 00:06:55,608
Yup, sure. I gotchu fam.
One can of premo kitty chow.

127
00:06:55,692 --> 00:06:57,983
Comin' right up!

128
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:02,108
Ugh! How do real cats stand not
being able to talk all the time?

129
00:07:02,192 --> 00:07:04,900
It seems like she wasn't
that hungry after all.

130
00:07:04,983 --> 00:07:06,858
[HINATA] Are you sure that
you know what she wants?

131
00:07:06,942 --> 00:07:08,567
Oh, I can tell.

132
00:07:08,650 --> 00:07:10,483
Just gaze directly
into their eyes.

133
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:12,317
Love needs no words.

134
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:15,233
Cats express it
with a single look.

135
00:07:15,317 --> 00:07:17,192
Ah. I'm sorry.

136
00:07:17,275 --> 00:07:19,317
Perhaps that's too
profound for you all.

137
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,608
Hinata. Take these lessons
to heart, my child.

138
00:07:21,692 --> 00:07:23,358
[HINATA]
Me? Uh, yeah, sure.

139
00:07:23,442 --> 00:07:25,150
[sighs]

140
00:07:27,858 --> 00:07:30,775
Let's call it.
We'll go out again tomorrow.

141
00:07:32,608 --> 00:07:33,817
[ALL gasp]

142
00:07:34,858 --> 00:07:37,442
[RYO]
It's a stuffed animal.

143
00:07:37,525 --> 00:07:40,733
[HINATA sighs]
What a relief!

144
00:07:40,817 --> 00:07:43,442
[RYO] This must be the
work of our cat abuser.

145
00:07:43,525 --> 00:07:45,233
Apparently, he's not
thrilled we're onto him,

146
00:07:45,317 --> 00:07:46,483
and wants us to know it.

147
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:47,358
Man.

148
00:07:47,442 --> 00:07:48,483
That's a possibility,

149
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:50,233
but we can't jump
to conclusions.

150
00:07:50,317 --> 00:07:52,192
I absolutely concur.

151
00:07:52,275 --> 00:07:55,150
But if we can get a look at
that security camera's footage,

152
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:57,192
we might have our answer.

153
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,233
[RYO] I'm gonna get you,
you bastard.

154
00:08:00,317 --> 00:08:03,150
I'll go ask the security
guard to help us.

155
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,983
You guys can head on home.

156
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:07,817
Listen. I can't stop you,
but please take care.

157
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:09,983
You tend to act rashly without
thinking when you're heated,

158
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,692
so don't get hurt
out there, all right?

159
00:08:11,775 --> 00:08:13,817
It's him who's gonna get hurt!

160
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:18,650
[SATSUMA] Why did the
suspect bother leaving

161
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:21,358
a threat in plain sight
for us to find?

162
00:08:21,442 --> 00:08:23,317
For someone whose goal
it is to harm cats,

163
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,400
they're drawing a lot of
attention to themselves.

164
00:08:26,483 --> 00:08:27,942
[RYO]
Come on, please!

165
00:08:28,025 --> 00:08:30,900
Sorry, but I can't.
Those are the rules, kid.

166
00:08:30,983 --> 00:08:34,817
[KONISHI] What's going on
over here? Hey!

167
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:38,150
Huh? Konishi, yo, what's up!

168
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:41,192
Man, I really lucked out!
I had no idea you worked here!

169
00:08:41,275 --> 00:08:43,025
A former delinquent
turned security guard,

170
00:08:43,108 --> 00:08:44,442
way to move up in the world!

171
00:08:44,525 --> 00:08:47,192
Well, I had to grow up and
be an adult at some point.

172
00:08:47,275 --> 00:08:49,192
I'm doing you a favor
since you're an old friend,

173
00:08:49,275 --> 00:08:50,608
but keep it quiet, all right?

174
00:08:50,692 --> 00:08:52,358
Thanks a ton, buddy!

175
00:08:52,442 --> 00:08:56,067
Let me rewind the tape
earlier today, and...

176
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:58,150
[RYO gasps]
The guy in the gray hoodie!

177
00:09:02,692 --> 00:09:04,358
That's him.

178
00:09:09,025 --> 00:09:11,275
[RYO]
He might still be nearby.

179
00:09:12,483 --> 00:09:14,567
Ryo! I saw the suspect!

180
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:17,775
He was wearing a gray hoodie,
just like the others said!

181
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:21,400
Sorry, I don't have time to
play today. Later, kitty.

182
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,650
Hey! What's up?

183
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:26,942
[BLACK CAT]
This way!

184
00:09:27,025 --> 00:09:30,275
Hang on, are you
telling me to follow you?

185
00:09:34,275 --> 00:09:36,025
Just a little further!

186
00:09:37,108 --> 00:09:38,317
[gasps]

187
00:09:41,483 --> 00:09:43,525
End of the line, asshole!

188
00:09:43,608 --> 00:09:45,650
What? Who the hell
do you think you are?

189
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,650
Huh? Ryo, what's up?

190
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:51,650
Satoru! You slime!
You're the one abusing cats?

191
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:55,692
Cats? No way. I've got
a cat of my own, see?

192
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:01,192
Okay, that's enough
evidence, I believe you.

193
00:10:01,275 --> 00:10:02,317
I'll let you go.

194
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,817
Just don't ever wear
this hoodie again!

195
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:05,442
Wait. Hang on,
what's the problem?

196
00:10:05,525 --> 00:10:07,233
Just put it in your
closet for a bit!

197
00:10:07,317 --> 00:10:11,942
What the hell was he
goin' on about? [sneezes]

198
00:10:12,025 --> 00:10:14,108
You like to hit cats,
ya sick freak?

199
00:10:14,192 --> 00:10:15,983
Let me go, man!

200
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:17,483
Why're you hurting
the strays, man?

201
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:19,983
Ow! Someone help!

202
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:21,900
[POLICE 9A]
Hey, stop right there, kid!

203
00:10:21,983 --> 00:10:23,150
Huh?

204
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,775
You're coming with me to
the station, right now!

205
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:26,775
[RYO groans]

206
00:10:26,858 --> 00:10:28,233
Listen, officer,
if you're done with

207
00:10:28,317 --> 00:10:29,442
all the stupid questions,

208
00:10:29,525 --> 00:10:31,650
I've got an animal
abuser to hunt down!

209
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:35,150
Look, kid. Your record's
not spotless.

210
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:37,025
What are your parents'
phone numbers?

211
00:10:37,108 --> 00:10:40,317
I'll be good. Don't call
my parents, please.

212
00:10:42,483 --> 00:10:44,650
My name's Mitsuki,
I'm Ryo's classmate.

213
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:46,192
I apologize.

214
00:10:46,275 --> 00:10:48,942
I'm sorry for the trouble he's
caused you tonight, officer.

215
00:10:49,025 --> 00:10:50,317
[SATSUMA]
You idiot!

216
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,233
What were you thinking,
randomly going out

217
00:10:52,317 --> 00:10:54,567
and attacking people on the
street like some vigilante?

218
00:10:54,650 --> 00:10:56,942
[RYO] Calm down,
I already said I was sorry.

219
00:10:57,025 --> 00:10:59,442
[SATSUMA] This is exactly
what we told you not to do!

220
00:10:59,525 --> 00:11:00,692
What were you even doing?

221
00:11:00,775 --> 00:11:01,775
[RYO]
The black cat with the collar

222
00:11:01,858 --> 00:11:02,858
was trying to tell me something.

223
00:11:02,942 --> 00:11:04,275
[SATSUMA]
Do you even hear yourself?

224
00:11:04,358 --> 00:11:06,150
You sound completely delusional!

225
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:09,442
I'm not delusional!
She was trying to help, I swear!

226
00:11:09,525 --> 00:11:11,108
That is quite enough, Ryo.

227
00:11:11,192 --> 00:11:13,483
Do you know how many club
points we lost because of you?

228
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:14,817
Huh?

229
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,317
As far as I've been told,

230
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,817
the police contacted the school
regarding what happened.

231
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,525
The entire club's hard work.

232
00:11:20,608 --> 00:11:24,025
Ruined because you decided
to act reckless and selfish.

233
00:11:24,108 --> 00:11:26,483
And all because of a cat.

234
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:29,067
What the hell's that
supposed to mean?

235
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,775
How dare you say something
so insensitive in front of me!

236
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:33,900
Their lives matter,
just as much as ours!

237
00:11:33,983 --> 00:11:36,692
Guys! Please, just
calm down a second!

238
00:11:36,775 --> 00:11:39,192
Don't bother coming out
with the kitty patrol anymore.

239
00:11:39,275 --> 00:11:41,567
Just stay back
in the dorm, Ryo.

240
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:44,442
[RYO] What? You orderin'
me around, specs?

241
00:11:44,525 --> 00:11:47,233
No. That's not an
order from Satsuma.

242
00:11:47,317 --> 00:11:48,817
It's from the school.

243
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:51,567
You've been suspended
for the next seven days.

244
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:52,942
[gasps]

245
00:11:55,775 --> 00:11:59,108
[RYO]
Damn it! Ow.

246
00:12:00,192 --> 00:12:02,567
[meows]

247
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:13,483
[BLACK CAT meows]

248
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:15,108
Are you worried
about li'l ol' me?

249
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:16,733
I appreciate it, girl.

250
00:12:16,817 --> 00:12:18,525
--[rustling]
--Huh?

251
00:12:19,775 --> 00:12:21,192
[CATS meowing]

252
00:12:21,275 --> 00:12:22,192
Hey!

253
00:12:22,275 --> 00:12:24,692
We came to cheer Ryo up!

254
00:12:24,775 --> 00:12:28,567
That weird guy is scary,
but we couldn't stay still!

255
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:30,983
You guys.

256
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:33,025
[RYO] Hey, it's been
a while, kitty cats!

257
00:12:33,108 --> 00:12:34,692
Are you all keepin' safe?

258
00:12:34,775 --> 00:12:36,067
[CATS meow]

259
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:38,525
[RYO] Are you the kitty
that got hurt that day?

260
00:12:38,608 --> 00:12:39,775
[meows]

261
00:12:39,858 --> 00:12:43,192
Looks like you healed up
quick. Thank goodness!

262
00:12:43,275 --> 00:12:46,483
Uncle Satsuma must've
taken good care of you.

263
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:48,775
[SATSUMA]
And all because of a cat.

264
00:12:48,858 --> 00:12:50,858
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

265
00:12:50,942 --> 00:12:54,317
How dare you say something
so insensitive in front of me!

266
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:58,317
[RYO]
I lost my temper back there.

267
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:01,900
But I know that he actually
cares about you guys, too.

268
00:13:01,983 --> 00:13:03,358
I overreacted.

269
00:13:03,442 --> 00:13:04,567
[meows]

270
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:07,900
I know! I should fix that up.

271
00:13:12,275 --> 00:13:15,317
This is why I love
him so much. So kind!

272
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,483
[CATS meow]

273
00:13:18,567 --> 00:13:21,608
[RYO] There, all better.
It does make me worry about

274
00:13:21,692 --> 00:13:24,608
what this guy's gonna
do next, though.

275
00:13:24,692 --> 00:13:27,233
Maybe you guys should
all just stay in here.

276
00:13:27,317 --> 00:13:32,067
But this place doesn't exactly
have a lot of room for you. Ah!

277
00:13:36,108 --> 00:13:38,358
[SATSUMA] There haven't been
reports of new incidents,

278
00:13:38,442 --> 00:13:41,608
and the kitty patrol hasn't
turned up any information.

279
00:13:41,692 --> 00:13:43,733
Could it be that the suspect

280
00:13:43,817 --> 00:13:46,358
wasn't targeting cats
in the first place?

281
00:13:51,858 --> 00:13:53,317
I'm on suspension.

282
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,483
So you guys gotta
keep quiet, okay?

283
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:58,108
Or Papa Ryo will
be in big trouble.

284
00:13:59,817 --> 00:14:01,692
Is someone out there?

285
00:14:03,817 --> 00:14:05,108
I swear.

286
00:14:05,192 --> 00:14:08,025
I had the strangest feeling
someone was watching me.

287
00:14:08,108 --> 00:14:09,608
I guess not.

288
00:14:12,775 --> 00:14:14,983
[MANAGER 9A]
Uh, hey, Saku.

289
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:18,483
Could you do me a favor and cut
the bread a little bit thinner?

290
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:21,275
Okay, but I thought I was
already cutting it pretty thin.

291
00:14:21,358 --> 00:14:22,400
Are you sure?

292
00:14:22,483 --> 00:14:24,983
It won't look like
the picture anymore.

293
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,150
Yeah, I know that.

294
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:30,108
But we're struggling
right now, so we have to.

295
00:14:30,192 --> 00:14:32,567
[phone rings]

296
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:35,067
Yes? May I take
your order please?

297
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:40,400
Oh. Hey, Ryo, what's up?
This is surprising. What?!

298
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:46,775
[panting] Could you take
care of these cats for me?

299
00:14:46,858 --> 00:14:49,692
Actually, my manager
won't allow animals in here.

300
00:14:49,775 --> 00:14:53,108
[RYO] Yeah, I know that, man!
But they're all in danger!

301
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:54,983
There are little lives at stake!

302
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:59,650
"Lives at stake"?
Seriously? But, still, I...

303
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:01,400
Huh? Cats?

304
00:15:02,483 --> 00:15:05,817
[MANAGER 9A]
A karaoke and cat cafe combo.

305
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:08,108
That's genius!

306
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:14,858
Okay. Now I just need to
round up the other cats.

307
00:15:14,942 --> 00:15:15,858
[BLACK CAT meows]

308
00:15:15,942 --> 00:15:17,733
Aww, you thirsty, girl?

309
00:15:23,317 --> 00:15:26,942
[BLACK CAT meows]

310
00:15:27,025 --> 00:15:28,233
Hey!

311
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:31,400
What the hell are you doing?

312
00:15:31,483 --> 00:15:33,150
You'd better let
her go immediately!

313
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:34,858
You always did have
a hair trigger

314
00:15:34,942 --> 00:15:37,025
when people messed with cats.

315
00:15:38,483 --> 00:15:39,942
That voice.

316
00:15:40,942 --> 00:15:43,025
[RYO]
Konishi?

317
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,775
But why?

318
00:15:44,858 --> 00:15:47,025
'Cause it's about damn
time you paid the price

319
00:15:47,108 --> 00:15:48,567
for what you did to me, Ryo.

320
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:49,900
What do you mean?

321
00:15:49,983 --> 00:15:51,942
--[BLACK CAT hisses]
--[KONISHI groans]

322
00:15:52,025 --> 00:15:52,942
You okay, girl?

323
00:15:53,025 --> 00:15:58,692
[BLACK CAT meows, growls]

324
00:15:58,775 --> 00:16:01,483
If you hate me for something,
let's deal with it man-to-man.

325
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:04,442
Leave the cats
out of your grudge!

326
00:16:04,525 --> 00:16:05,692
Come with me.

327
00:16:05,775 --> 00:16:07,692
And why should I?

328
00:16:07,775 --> 00:16:09,858
Neither of us want
the cops involved.

329
00:16:09,942 --> 00:16:11,942
Let's go have a little
chat at the warehouse

330
00:16:12,025 --> 00:16:13,442
where the gang used to meet up.

331
00:16:13,525 --> 00:16:14,900
Fine, then.

332
00:16:17,025 --> 00:16:19,067
You stay here, kitty. Be safe.

333
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:20,942
[BLACK CAT meows]

334
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,067
[BLACK CAT]
What should I do?

335
00:16:31,525 --> 00:16:32,525
[BLACK CAT]
This is bad.

336
00:16:32,608 --> 00:16:35,317
I've gotta help Ryo,
no matter what!

337
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,400
[SATSUMA] ♪ Why do we
keep passing right by, ♪

338
00:16:37,483 --> 00:16:39,108
♪ Like ships within the night? ♪

339
00:16:39,192 --> 00:16:44,025
♪ If we keep this up my feelings
will never reach your heart ♪

340
00:16:44,108 --> 00:16:47,608
[BLACK CAT meowing]
Satsuma! Open up!

341
00:16:47,692 --> 00:16:50,942
Hello. Huh?

342
00:16:51,025 --> 00:16:52,525
No time to explain, let's go!

343
00:16:52,608 --> 00:16:55,067
[SATSUMA] Why're you here?
Aren't you at the wrong room?

344
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,733
[BLACK CAT]
Please, we have to leave, now!

345
00:16:56,817 --> 00:16:59,192
Shh. Settle down.
We're not allowed

346
00:16:59,275 --> 00:17:00,692
to have pets in this place.

347
00:17:00,775 --> 00:17:02,817
I could take you to Ryo's room
if that'll calm you down.

348
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:06,692
Would you listen
to me? Ryo is in danger!

349
00:17:07,692 --> 00:17:08,858
What?

350
00:17:09,983 --> 00:17:12,233
He's planning on confronting
the culprit alone!

351
00:17:12,317 --> 00:17:13,650
He needs our help!

352
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:16,650
Hold on. You can talk?

353
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:18,150
[BLACK CAT]
Shut up, nerd!

354
00:17:18,233 --> 00:17:20,650
We need to hurry to
the warehouse by the river!

355
00:17:20,733 --> 00:17:25,650
[SATSUMA panting]

356
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:30,150
[SATSUMA] The cat can talk, the
cat can talk, the cat can talk!

357
00:17:33,817 --> 00:17:36,983
[BLACK CAT gasps]
Oh no! The admins found me!

358
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:40,233
Ryo!

359
00:17:50,233 --> 00:17:52,692
So what's this all about, then?

360
00:17:52,775 --> 00:17:55,858
Three years ago. I decided to
go and buy some new clothes

361
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:57,483
with what little
money I had.

362
00:17:57,567 --> 00:18:00,942
[KONISHI]
This one? Or maybe that one?

363
00:18:01,025 --> 00:18:03,192
Damn! Shopping's brutal, man!

364
00:18:03,275 --> 00:18:04,442
[GIRLS squeal]

365
00:18:04,525 --> 00:18:05,817
[GIRL 9B]
Omigosh, it's Ryo!

366
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:07,567
Hey, Ryo! C'mere a second!

367
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:09,692
Konishi? What's up?

368
00:18:09,775 --> 00:18:12,567
Tell me the truth, bruh.
Which one of these sick bombers

369
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:14,442
do you think I would
look the coolest in?

370
00:18:14,525 --> 00:18:16,608
You're asking me
for fashion advice?

371
00:18:16,692 --> 00:18:21,442
Lemme see. Um. I'd go with that!

372
00:18:21,525 --> 00:18:23,692
Wait. For real?

373
00:18:23,775 --> 00:18:25,608
Trust me, it's lit!

374
00:18:25,692 --> 00:18:28,150
[KONISHI]
"Lit" huh.

375
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:33,817
[gasps] What in the world
is with that lame sweater?

376
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:36,942
[KONISHI sobs]
My life became a living hell

377
00:18:37,025 --> 00:18:38,442
from that moment forward.

378
00:18:38,525 --> 00:18:40,733
My girlfriend dumped
me like I was trash.

379
00:18:40,817 --> 00:18:43,608
People on the street pointed
and called me a freak!

380
00:18:43,692 --> 00:18:46,192
Whoa. Are you serious?

381
00:18:46,275 --> 00:18:48,317
All because you,
the popular bully,

382
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,775
decided to trick me for a laugh.

383
00:18:50,858 --> 00:18:53,608
After that, the breakup
rocked my world so badly

384
00:18:53,692 --> 00:18:56,317
that I dropped out of middle
school and went to work.

385
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,442
But then I saw you
at school, and the pain of

386
00:18:58,525 --> 00:19:01,025
you tormenting me
came rushing back.

387
00:19:01,108 --> 00:19:03,775
I won't be satisfied
until I have my revenge!

388
00:19:03,858 --> 00:19:08,275
Look, Konishi. I'm really
sorry about all of that!

389
00:19:08,358 --> 00:19:10,067
But, listen.

390
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:13,025
I really did think that sweater
was going to look great on you

391
00:19:13,108 --> 00:19:15,442
when I pointed it out
to you back then.

392
00:19:15,525 --> 00:19:18,525
You think you can mock
me again, you asshole?

393
00:19:18,608 --> 00:19:20,525
I'm gonna beat you
to a bloody pulp!

394
00:19:20,608 --> 00:19:22,692
You and those cats
you love so much!

395
00:19:22,775 --> 00:19:26,025
Okay. You can beat me up.

396
00:19:26,108 --> 00:19:27,608
But not the cats. Please--

397
00:19:27,692 --> 00:19:29,858
--[thud]
--[SATSUMA grunts]

398
00:19:31,525 --> 00:19:33,400
[SATSUMA]
Hold it right there!

399
00:19:34,525 --> 00:19:38,983
Oh no. My glasses. I can't see.

400
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:40,983
Satsuma? Uh...

401
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:42,275
[SATSUMA]
My glasses. Where are--

402
00:19:42,358 --> 00:19:43,483
[SATSUMA gasps]

403
00:19:45,983 --> 00:19:48,233
[SATSUMA] Halt! I have come
to solve this dispute!

404
00:19:48,317 --> 00:19:49,567
I overheard your conversation,

405
00:19:49,650 --> 00:19:51,275
and with the power
of rationality,

406
00:19:51,358 --> 00:19:53,650
I can deduce that Ryo
was completely serious

407
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:55,983
all those years ago when he
chose that sweater for you.

408
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:59,025
And that's because... Behold!

409
00:19:59,108 --> 00:20:00,317
[gasps]

410
00:20:01,650 --> 00:20:03,525
[KONISHI]
It's hideous!

411
00:20:03,608 --> 00:20:06,233
Yes. Ryo still has
the same awful taste now

412
00:20:06,317 --> 00:20:07,358
as he did back then.

413
00:20:07,442 --> 00:20:08,775
Horrific, I know.

414
00:20:08,858 --> 00:20:11,025
So you see, you're
partially at fault here,

415
00:20:11,108 --> 00:20:12,567
for trusting in
his fashion sense

416
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:15,817
based on no other facts except
his popularity with women.

417
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,067
[gasps]

418
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:18,900
[SATSUMA] Besides, the
experience did you good,

419
00:20:18,983 --> 00:20:20,567
wouldn't you agree?

420
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:23,317
Oversized hoodies like that
one are in style right now.

421
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,442
That look is,
indeed, quite "lit."

422
00:20:25,525 --> 00:20:27,692
Listening to this idiot
may have ruined your date,

423
00:20:27,775 --> 00:20:29,025
but you learned
from your mistake,

424
00:20:29,108 --> 00:20:30,650
so you're better off
now than when you

425
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:33,108
naively followed his
suggestions, right?

426
00:20:33,192 --> 00:20:34,317
Hmph.

427
00:20:40,317 --> 00:20:42,233
I guess I owe you
my thanks, man.

428
00:20:42,317 --> 00:20:44,108
I managed to work things
out with Konishi.

429
00:20:44,192 --> 00:20:45,858
So I guess the cats
are safe now.

430
00:20:45,942 --> 00:20:50,733
That's good. But no sign
of the black cat?

431
00:20:50,817 --> 00:20:54,275
Nothing. I wonder
where she ran off to.

432
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,692
[SATSUMA] That reminds me.
There's something I said to you

433
00:20:57,775 --> 00:20:59,733
before that I'd
like to take back.

434
00:20:59,817 --> 00:21:01,942
I see now that you
really aren't delusional.

435
00:21:02,025 --> 00:21:03,983
That you can actually
understand cats.

436
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:05,525
Because I also heard her voice.

437
00:21:05,608 --> 00:21:07,483
That black cat clearly
told me to save you.

438
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:10,442
Wow! So you finally
get it, Satsuma.

439
00:21:10,525 --> 00:21:12,525
Now you see.
Cats can communicate

440
00:21:12,608 --> 00:21:14,858
with your soul with
a single, precious look!

441
00:21:14,942 --> 00:21:16,442
Uh, no.

442
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,358
That's not what I'm saying, I
mean she literally spoke to me.

443
00:21:18,442 --> 00:21:20,233
And here I thought
I was the only person

444
00:21:20,317 --> 00:21:23,025
worthy of being called
the Cat Whisperer.

445
00:21:23,108 --> 00:21:24,983
I wish she'd come back.

446
00:21:27,192 --> 00:21:28,525
Anyway.

447
00:21:28,608 --> 00:21:30,858
It's good this school has
uniforms, don't you think?

448
00:21:30,942 --> 00:21:33,108
No one has to see your
terrible fashion sense.

449
00:21:33,192 --> 00:21:36,317
Screw you. We were
having a moment there!

450
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:39,608
Well. I'll be the bigger
man and compliment you!

451
00:21:39,692 --> 00:21:40,733
You looked very cute without

452
00:21:40,817 --> 00:21:42,983
your glasses on
back there, Satsuma.

453
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,983
You saw nothing,
do you understand?

454
00:21:45,067 --> 00:21:47,483
Oh, come on, there's no
need to be so bashful!

455
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:49,525
I was worried Ryo was
gonna be depressed for a bit,

456
00:21:49,608 --> 00:21:50,650
but he seems fine.

457
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:51,983
I think we can thank
Satsuma for that.

458
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:53,858
He really does lift his spirits.

459
00:21:53,942 --> 00:21:55,358
--[door opens]
--[BOTH] Huh?

460
00:21:55,442 --> 00:21:57,108
Here's your honey toast!

461
00:21:59,525 --> 00:22:00,942
[HINATA]
Why's it look thicker again?

462
00:22:01,025 --> 00:22:03,650
[SAKU]
Uh, long story.

463
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,233
[MITSUKI]
Did something happen?

464
00:23:35,317 --> 00:23:36,775
[KEISHI]
The government.

465
00:23:36,858 --> 00:23:39,817
They might be cracking down on
the 7th ward sometime soon.

466
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:41,775
[MITSUKI]
That's enough, all of you!

467
00:23:41,858 --> 00:23:44,483
I can't believe the selfishness
I'm hearing in this room!

468
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:47,983
Stop your bickering and
think about how they feel!

